{
  "text": "In all brain-injured animals, CCI resulted in a large cortical contusion cavity, a loss of hemispheric tissue and an increased size of the ipsilateral ventricle [CITATION_1] . To validate the accuracy of SectionToVolume, tissue from three sham-injured and three brain-injured animals were used to measure the area of hemispheric tissue, ventricle area in each hemisphere and the area of the cortical cavity. We then calculated the corresponding volumes and compared these results to those obtained using the ImageJ software.",
